<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="154">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181649" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole erethizon Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole erethizon Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erethizon">Pheidole erethizon</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="154">Types Mus. Comp. Zool. Harvard.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="154">
etymology NL 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181649" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole erethizon Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole erethizon Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erethizon">erethizon</taxonomicName>
, porcupine, referring to the very long, bristly pilosity of the major and minor.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="154">
Diagnosis A member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33688" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole crassicornis Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole crassicornis Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassicornis">crassicornis</taxonomicName>
group characterized in both the major and minor by exceptionally dense, long hair (reaching an extreme in the gastral pilosity of the major); and entire head (except frontal triangle and central piece of clypeus), mesosoma, and waist foveolate and opaque. In addition, the minor is unusual within the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33688" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole crassicornis Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole crassicornis Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassicornis">crassicornis</taxonomicName>
group in possessing a narrowed occiput seen in full-face view, yet nevertheless lacking a nuchal collar.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="154">measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 1.26, HL 1.34, SL 0.92, EL 0.22, PW 0.64.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="154">Paratype minor: HW 0.58, HL 0.70, SL 0.86, EL 0.16, PW 0.42.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="154">color Major: concolorous medium yellow with a very slight reddish tinge.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="154">Minor: concolorous medium yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="154">range Recorded from the type locality (Michoacan); Azizintla, Guerrero; and Miacatlan, Morelos.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
